.





Sincerely yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: KATHARINE A. WHITE

CC, 1 p.

Ithaca, N.Y.





April 4, 1957

Dear Katharine,

I am delighted you want my little ballad. Yes, of course, couldn't is better rhythmically than could not.

Let me thank you very warmly for your frank and charming letter about LOLITA. But after all how many are the memorable literary characters whom we would like our 'teen-age daughters to meet? Would you like our Patricia to go on a date with Othello? Would we like